[Installing jlibcpp]

:Makefile defines

ENABLE_DEBUG = <no, yes>
ENABLE_GRAPHICS = <directfb-nodeps, directfb, sdl2, sfml2, x11>
ENABLE_MEDIA = <gif, ilist, v4l2, alsa, libvlc, libav, libxine>

:Compiling

$ export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=<pkg-path>
$ sudo make all install

[Compilling tests]

For each module of jlibcpp, change to tests directory and type:

"make"

[Compiling applications]

## Makefile -- with pkgconfig -- begin ##

CFLAGS	= `pkg-config --cflags jlibcpp`
LIBS		= `pkg-config --libs jlibcpp`

all:
	g++ <app.cpp> -o <app> $(CFLAGS) $(LIBS)

## Makefile -- with pkgconfig -- end ##

:Dependencies

	libdirectfb, libsdl2, libsfml2, libx11, libasound2, libssl, uuid

:Problems

1. with ENABLE_MEDIA=libvlc the jmedia not working corretly with lua
R: disable or remove the lua plugin "/usr/lib/vlc/plugins/lua/liblua_plugin.so"

2. the directfb video provider (xine) not working properly
R: edit the file 'DirectFB/interfaces/IDirectFBVideoProvider/Makefile' and search 
	 for the definition $(XINE_LIBS) and swap for the $(XINE_VDPAU_LIBS). Finishing 
	 with 'make clean all install'

3. directfb video provider (libdirectfb) with problem
R: edit the file 'DirectFB/interfaces/IDirectFBVideoProvider/video_out_dfb/video_out_dfb.c'
	 at line 270 and change the old line ...
     
		 if (this->dest) {
	 
	   for this one ...
	
	   if (this->dest && this->dest->GetSize) {

4. jsystem::Beep() not working
R: enable pcspkr module as following:

	sudo modprobe pcspkr
	echo -e "\a"

5. the module sox no compile and print a message asking for -fpic
R: recompile libsox with the option "--enable-shared"

6. the events not working with (ENABLE_GRAPHICS == directfb*) and (ENABLE_MEDIA == libav)
R: this occurs because the directfb uses SDL and libav uses SDL2. try to edit Makefile.media and change 'sdl2' by 'sdl' in libav's compilation
